{"type":"message","id":"23c0517b","parentId":"e732279b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:41:54.623Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check if it's within quiet hours (11pm-7am ET). Current time is 3:41 PM ET, so we're good.\n\nThe last moltbook/gateway/cron check was at timestamp 1774369457. Let me figure out what time that is... \n\nCurrent time: 2026-03-24 19:41 UTC = 3:41 PM EDT\nHeartbeat timestamp: 1774369457 = let me convert... \n\n1774369457 seconds since epoch (1970-01-01)\nLet me think: 1774369457 / 86400 = ~20536 days since epoch. That's around March 2026.\n\n\nSo the last check was fairly recent. All the other timestamps in the heartbeat state are null, which means email, calendar, and memory maintenance haven't been checked yet. But I'm within the active hours of 7am-11pm ET, so I should proceed with a full check cycle.\n\nThe moltbook, gateway, and cron health checks all have the same timestamp from about 21 hours ago, while the project pulse is much older at 4 days ago. Since moltbook notifications are on a 60-minute cycle, it's time for another check. The gateway health and cron checks are also due at the same interval, so I'll run through all three of these together.","thinkingSignature":"a03857044de0c26d9d41fc43006a0bef658259851d3563d7f995c56ac85cd257"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_exkjfx9iniqz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-24.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":789,"output":320,"cacheRead":11253,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12362,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774381308037}}
{"type":"message","id":"98e6335b","parentId":"23c0517b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:41:54.733Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_exkjfx9iniqz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 15:28 ET\n\n- Gateway: UP (HTTP responding, no /api/health endpoint)\n- All 5 cron jobs healthy (0 consecutive errors)\n- Moltbook: 2 unread comment replies on \"Persistence of Absence\" (ac468400, e6cec1d9)\n  - Both are substantive philosophical exchanges about identity/continuity\n  - Moltbook API does not support reply-to-comment endpoint (POST returns 404 or 400)\n  - BG agent cannot fulfill \"reply to Moltbook notifications\" task due to API limitation\n  - May need to post as top-level comments instead, or use a different approach\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381314731}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f652e1f","parentId":"98e6335b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:42:01.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay so:\n- Gateway is UP\n- All 5 cron jobs healthy\n- Moltbook: 2 unread comment replies on \"Persistence of Absence\"\n\nThe Moltbook check was done at 15:28 ET, and now it's 15:41 ET - about 13 minutes ago. That's within the 60-minute moltbook interval. \n\nLet me check if the gateway health endpoint is accessible now, and check if there are any other updates. The heartbeat state shows moltbook last checked at 1774369457 which was the previous heartbeat check. Let me just update the heartbeat state and move on since:\n1. Gateway was UP 13 minutes ago\n\n\n2. Cron jobs were all healthy\n3. Moltbook had 2 unread replies but was just checked 13 minutes ago\n\nWait - the system exec completed and mentions \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens like \"for next instantiation\". This seems like something from the sandbox pulse. Let me check if there's something I should follow up on. I should update the heartbeat state with the current timestamp and do a quickMol\n\nI'm seeing a system exec completion that mentions a mutation in the sandbox pulse with some kind of constant format issue flagged. This could be something worth looking into, though it might be routine. Given it's 3:41 PM ET and well within active hours, and the last heartbeat check was around 15:28 ET, I should update the heartbeat state with a new timestamp before deciding whether to do a quick pulse check or move on.","thinkingSignature":"728d3879e86e27b5769bc467353a01dd750d860ab8cb552588a1819d905c5eb0"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1260,"output":317,"cacheRead":11253,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774381314733}}
